  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, there is no specific public information indicating whether Luis von Ahn, the co-founder and CEO of Duolingo, personally used Duolingo to learn a new language. However, given his deep involvement in the development and continuous improvement of the platform, it's reasonable to assume that he is familiar with its features and methodologies.\n\nLuis von Ahn is multilingual himself; he is fluent in both English and his native Spanish, and he has also demonstrated proficiency in other languages. His personal language skills likely stem from traditional language learning methods and his academic background rather than solely relying on Duolingo.\n\nThat said, as the leader of a language-learning platform, von Ahn has emphasized the importance of making education accessible and effective, which is reflected in Duolingo's user-friendly design and gamified learning approach. While he may not have used Duolingo to learn a new language from scratch, his expertise and insights have been pivotal in shaping the tool to benefit millions of learners worldwide.\n\nIf you're interested in more detailed or updated information, I recommend checking recent interviews or statements from Luis von Ahn where he might discuss his personal use of Duolingo or his language learning experiences.",
